    +semQuote("https://adrianroselli.com/2017/11/a-responsive-accessible-table.html#WrapToDo", "the article")
      block quote
        p.
          I ran through quite a lot above. For the most part you can copy and paste the CSS and JavaScript and use it as-is. However, you will need to customize just a few things for each table on your site. I've made a quick list of  what to do from all the bits above:

        ol
          li.
            Give your #[code &lt;table&gt;] an #[code id] attribute.
          li.
            Put the value of that #[code id] into the #[code aria-labelledby] on the wrapper.
          li.
            Identify the ideal width for the table in your print and screen media queries.
          li.
            Reset any cell text alignment for the smaller size.
          li.
            Choose an appropriate width for the cell label text in the #[code grid-template-columns] value.
    